# Documentation convention

This project maintains two parallel docs for every feature or decision:

- `docs/human/<topic>.md` — concise, non-technical, no code or jargon. Explains
  what it is and why it matters to a user.
- `docs/ai/<topic>.md` — technical and complete. Explains how it works: stack,
  data model, file paths, logic, trade-offs.

## Rules

- When you add or change a feature, update BOTH tracks in the same change.
- Keep the two docs consistent with each other and with the code.
- Register new topics in the table in `docs/README.md`.
- If a change clearly affects only one track, still confirm the other is accurate.

See `docs/README.md` for the full explanation.
